Prompted by previous results showing that postsynaptic proteins have been linked to the genetic susceptibility of schizophrenia (
 Fromer et al., 2014; 
 Fernández et al., 2009a; 
 Nithianantharajah et al., 2013; 
 Kirov et al., 2012; 
 Purcell et al., 2014), we hypothesized that TTTPs may be relevant to the age of onset of schizophrenia. For these analyses we examined multiple sets of publically available genetic data including de novo and GWAS data (see Materials and methods ‘Genes Lists’, 
 Supplementary file 1f) and applied multiple analytical approaches.
